* Install R
1. Download the most recent version of R.
2. Start the R program; 
3. As a first step with R, start the R help browser by typing help.start() in the R command window. For help on any function, e.g. the “mean” function, type ? mean.

* Users should install DESeq2 before using Xtail:
start R and enter:
source("https://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")
biocLite("DESeq2")


Then, users can install Xtail from source package or binary package:
* Install from source package
Download the source package from "releases" , e.g. xtail_1.1.3-source.tar.gz;
For Windows:
Before install, you need install "Rtools", "MainGW";     
Then using the following command to install: install.packages("xtail_1.1.3-source.tar.gz",repo=NULL,type="source")
Or, you can install directly from the github: install.packages("https://github.com/xryanglab/xtail/releases/download/v1.1.3/xtail_1.1.3-source.tar.gz",type="source")
For Linux or Mac:
install.packages("xtail_1.1.3-source.tar.gz"), or install.packages("https://github.com/xryanglab/xtail/releases/download/v1.1.3/xtail_1.1.3-source.tar.gz")


*  Installing from binary package (recommended)
Download the binary package from "releases", e.g. xtail_1.1.3.zip; 
For Windows and Mac OS X, users can install Xtail using R's package installer;
For linux, type the following in an R command window: install.packages("xtail_1.1.3.tar.gz"), or install.packages("https://github.com/xryanglab/xtail/releases/download/v1.1.3/xtail_1.1.3.tar.gz")
